==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Loup-garou
<hw>Loup`-ga`rou"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu>pl.
<plw>Loups-garous</plw> <pr>(#)</pr></plu>. <ety>[F., fr.
<ets>loup</ets> wolf + a Teutonic word akin to E.
<ets>werewolf</ets>.]</ety> <def>A werewolf; a lycanthrope.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><q>The superstition of the <qex>loup-garou</qex>, or werewolf,
belongs to the folklore of most modern nations, and has its reflex in
the story of ⟦ldquo⟧Little Red Riding-hood⟦rdquo⟧ and others.</q>
<rj><qau>Brinton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Louping</ent>⟦br⟧
